The Sokoto State Government on Saturday disbursed the sum of N14.68 million for the purchase of cows for orphans across the 86 districts of the state.

According to the Chairman, Sokoto State Zakkat and Endowment Commission, Malam Lawal Maidoki, the gesture was to enable them have splendid Sallah celebration like other children.

He said that each of the district would get not less than N160,000 to buy a cow and share its meat to orphans in their areas.

In his remarks, Sultan Saâ€™ad Abubakar III, commended the district heads for their dedication in ensuring the success of the programme in their various domain.